    <div class="portfolio_head">
     <h1 id="portfolio_headText">
      Hydrologic
      <br />
     </h1>
     <h1 id="portfolio_subText">
      Watershed States of America
      <br />
     </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="portfolio_desc">
     <h3 id="portfolio_descText">
      This web mapping project sets aside the continental United States' existing political divisions and replaces them with watershed boundaries. In a time when the American West is facing water management challenges in the face of a severe drought, these maps present the US with a set of borders that align with, rather than cut across, the country's increasingly precious water resources. The map operates at three scales, each emphasizing a different aspect of the story. The widest view focuses on the major rivers and landforms that shape watershed boundaries. An intermediate scale identifies broad population patterns and identifies areas of irrigated agriculture. The final scale shows settlement patterns at a more detailed level and adds additional river and new dam information.
      <br />
      <br />
     </h3>
     <h3 id="portfolio_bigLink">
